data.content:
Three things break in EF Core 10. Here's each issue and its fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — no longer accepts expression trees

The setter parameter changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`. Your manual expression tree code **won't compile**.

**Fix** — replace with a simple lambda:
```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type columns — naming changes (two sub-issues)

**a) Column uniquification:** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one `Street` column silently. EF 10 auto-appends a number (`Street`, `Street1`). This will generate a migration that **renames columns and can break existing data**.

**Fix** — pin column names explicitly:
```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types use full path:** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was column `BillingAddress_City`, now becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix** — pin the old name:
```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods like `CommandReaderExecuting` now require an extra `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging).

**Fix** — add the parameter:
```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection,
    DbCommand command,
    DbContext context,
    Guid commandId,
    Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)   // ← new
{
    // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
    // Use command.CommandText for actual execution SQL
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
